Request Body
{
"name":"scott", 
"gender":"male", 
"email":"abc@gmail.com", 
"status":"active"
}

Now to generate random name and email address please user the below script
And add this script in the Pre-Request script
var random=Math.random().toString(36).substring(2);

var useremail="jim"+random+"@gmail.com";
var username="jim"+random;

Also create an environment variable
pm.environment.set("email_env","useremail");
pm.environment.set("name_env",username);

now we are going to refer the environment variables in the body
{
"name":"{{name_env}}", 
"gender":"male", 
"email":"{{email_env}}", 
"status":"active"
}

Now the get response and store the ID in the environment.
Now the below script save in the test and click on save. 
var jsonData=JSON.parse(responseBody);
pm.environment.set("userid_env",jsonData.id);

Now in the get request you need to add this URL
https://gorest.co.in/public/v2/users/{{userid_env}}

Now in the post script of get user you need to add the below script to compare the values which you passed in the pre-request script in the create user request.

//validating json field in the response
pm.test("values of json fields", () =>{
    var jsonData=pm.response.json();

    pm.expect(jsonData.id).to.eql(pm.environment.get("userid_env"))
    pm.expect(jsonData.email).to.eql(pm.environment.get("email_env"))
    pm.expect(jsonData.name).to.eql(pm.environment.get("username_env"))
}
);

Now in the update user request you need to pass same information in the pre request script To generate random user details
var random=Math.random().toString(36).substring(2);

var useremail="jim"+random+"@gmail.com";
var username="jim"+random;

pm.environment.set("email_env","useremail");
pm.environment.set("name_env",username);

And in the update user request body paste the below script

{
"name":"{{name_env}}", 
"email":"{{email_env}}", 
"status":"inactive"
}

And Delete user request just pass this URL
https://gorest.co.in/public/v2/users/{{userid_env}}

Also, in the post request of Delete request you need to add below script to remove variables
pm.environment.unset("email_env");
pm.environment.unset("name_env");
pm.environment.unset("userid_env");

Note : The above steps which we made we cannot execute particular request because everything is dependent on other requests. So, we need to run the collections.


